WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.959 --> 00:00:07.920
This programme
contains some strong language.

2
00:00:37.879 --> 00:00:40.080
Ooh. sweetheart.
Haven't got enough. you didn't order.

3
00:00:40.080 --> 00:00:42.879
Well. I've only
just arrived. so tough.

4
00:00:42.879 --> 00:00:45.319
Well. what do I do now?

5
00:00:45.319 --> 00:00:47.680
Who is it? Dunno. some bloke.

6
00:00:50.120 --> 00:00:52.359
You going to Slimbo's on Friday?

7
00:00:52.359 --> 00:00:54.079
What is it. drinks?

8
00:00:54.079 --> 00:00:56.119
Bit of a pizza. I think.
Might do. yeah.

9
00:00:58.880 --> 00:01:00.559
What's happening there. then?

10
00:01:06.520 --> 00:01:11.920
Move back. if you could. thank you.
Back you go. that's it. back you go.
What's going on?

11
00:01:13.399 --> 00:01:15.279
What's happening?

12
00:01:15.279 --> 00:01:16.920
Buggered if I know.
It's orders from above.

13
00:01:16.920 --> 00:01:20.320
But the body's still in
there though. isn't it?
We can't just leave it.

14
00:01:20.320 --> 00:01:21.919
Move back. they said. clear the site.

15
00:01:21.919 --> 00:01:23.559
Special access. they said.

16
00:01:23.559 --> 00:01:25.440
For who? Torchwood.

17
00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:48.600
Who's Torchwood?
Special ops or something.

18
00:01:48.600 --> 00:01:50.799
Is that hot? Er. yeah.

19
00:01:50.799 --> 00:01:54.679
They're not allowed in. they could
contaminate the evidence.
How come...?

20
00:01:54.679 --> 00:01:57.120
Don't ask me.
there's no procedure any more.

21
00:01:57.120 --> 00:01:59.119
It's a fucking disgrace.

22
00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:42.919
There you go. I can taste it.

23
00:02:42.919 --> 00:02:45.679
Oestrogen. definitely oestrogen.

24
00:02:47.160 --> 00:02:52.399
You take the Pill. flush it away.
it enters the water cycle.
feminises the fish.

25
00:02:52.399 --> 00:02:57.079
goes all the way up into the sky.
then falls all the way
back down on to me.

26
00:02:57.079 --> 00:03:00.799
Contraceptives in the rain.

27
00:03:00.799 --> 00:03:02.639
Love this planet.

28
00:03:02.639 --> 00:03:05.200
Still. at least I won't get pregnant.

29
00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:07.000
Never doing that again.

30
00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:09.000
How's it going?

31
00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:15.319
Nothing yet. It's got to connect.
I've just got to feel it. Hurry up!
I'm freezing my arse off.

32
00:03:15.319 --> 00:03:20.199
I can't just flick a switch.
it's more like it grants me access.

33
00:03:20.199 --> 00:03:24.679
Whatever that means.
It's like... Oh. oh. oh!

34
00:03:24.679 --> 00:03:28.559
Positions. If I get punched again.
I'm punching it right back.

35
00:03:28.559 --> 00:03:30.720
Just. concentrate. Suzie?

36
00:03:47.680 --> 00:03:49.920
There was... What was?

37
00:03:49.920 --> 00:03:53.519
I was..
Oh. my God. I was going home.

38
00:03:53.519 --> 00:03:59.320
Listen to me. we've only got two
minutes so it's important that you
listen. OK? Who are you? Trust me.

39
00:03:59.320 --> 00:04:03.520
You're dead.
How am I dead? You were stabbed.
I'm not dead. I can see you.

40
00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:08.440
We've brought you back but we haven't
got long. I'm sorry but you've got
to concentrate. who did this to you?

41
00:04:08.440 --> 00:04:11.119
What did you see? Why am I dead?
Who attacked you?

42
00:04:11.119 --> 00:04:13.399
I don't want to be dead.
Sixty seconds.

43
00:04:13.399 --> 00:04:19.439
You've got to think. just focus on
me. What was the last thing you saw?
I didn't see...

44
00:04:19.439 --> 00:04:21.920
I don't know.
Who killed you. did you see them?

45
00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:24.880
I don't know.
There was...something behind me.

46
00:04:24.880 --> 00:04:30.080
Police said
one stab wound in the back.
So you didn't see anything? No.

47
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:36.039
What happens now?

48
00:04:36.039 --> 00:04:39.399
Thirty seconds. But he didn't
see anyone. Don't waste it.

49
00:04:39.399 --> 00:04:42.040
What else do I say?

50
00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:45.040
What's your name?

51
00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:48.600
John. John Tucker. OK. John.

52
00:04:50.439 --> 00:04:54.400
Not long now. Who are you?
Captain Jack Harkness. Tell me...

53
00:04:54.400 --> 00:04:56.879
what was it like when you died?
What did you see?

54
00:04:58.999 --> 00:05:00.559
John.

55
00:05:00.559 --> 00:05:03.119
Tell me what you saw.

56
00:05:03.119 --> 00:05:05.359
Ten seconds.

57
00:05:05.359 --> 00:05:09.040
Nothing. I saw nothing.

58
00:05:10.680 --> 00:05:12.520
Oh. my God. There's nothing.

59
00:05:19.119 --> 00:05:21.280
Shit.

60
00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:24.199
I said it was stupid. telling
him he was dead. Well. you try it.

61
00:05:24.199 --> 00:05:26.280
"Trust me". like that's gonna work.

62
00:05:26.280 --> 00:05:32.440
Told the last corpse he was injured.
he wasted the whole two minutes
screaming for an ambulance.

63
00:05:32.440 --> 00:05:35.440
Maybe there's no right way
of doing it.

64
00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:36.960
What do you think?

65
00:06:22.840 --> 00:06:25.960
You still up?

66
00:06:25.960 --> 00:06:27.480
In here.

67
00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:31.880
They said on the news. murder in the
city centre. were you there?

68
00:06:32.959 --> 00:06:35.279
No. I dunno. nothing to do with me.

69
00:06:35.279 --> 00:06:38.479
How come you're still up though?
Banana Boat came round.

70
00:06:38.479 --> 00:06:42.840
He was saying he's got plans.
he's off again next summer.

71
00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:45.079
How come you're not pissed then?

72
00:06:45.079 --> 00:06:47.079
No. we had a cup of tea.

73
00:06:47.079 --> 00:06:49.959
He's read this thing about diabetes.

74
00:06:49.959 --> 00:06:52.680
Me and him having tea.

75
00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:56.199
that's middle age. that is.
There's some Chinese in the fridge.

76
00:06:56.199 --> 00:07:00.399
No. I'm knackered. You coming
to bed? I'll just finish here.

77
00:07:00.399 --> 00:07:03.040
This man's found his sister.

78
00:07:05.359 --> 00:07:07.480
I'll see you in a minute.

79
00:07:29.999 --> 00:07:34.039
Von. can you do a search for me?
Oh. join the queue.

80
00:07:34.039 --> 00:07:37.920
It's a Captain Jack Harkness.
Could you check him out? I'm busy.
There's proper channels. Gwen.

81
00:07:37.920 --> 00:07:43.480
What sort of Captain?
Don't know. Just Captain.
If I've got time. Thanks! If!

82
00:07:43.480 --> 00:07:47.799
Sarah Pallister. 72.
murdered in her front room.

83
00:07:47.799 --> 00:07:51.760
Rani Ghosh. 45.
murdered in Robintree Alley.

84
00:07:51.760 --> 00:07:56.399
And now John Tucker. 19.
murdered in Llangyfelach Lane.

85
00:07:56.399 --> 00:08:01.120
So far. there's absolutely nothing
linking these three victims.
apart from the way they died.

86
00:08:01.120 --> 00:08:03.640
As far as we can tell.
all with the same weapon.

87
00:08:03.640 --> 00:08:06.880
A blade. approximately eight
inches long. three inches deep.

88
00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:12.079
The women were stabbed from the
front. but Tucker from behind. What
does that tell us about the killer?

89
00:08:12.079 --> 00:08:13.679
That he's a coward.

90
00:08:15.240 --> 00:08:19.120
But those people last night. the
people in the car. who were they?

91
00:08:19.120 --> 00:08:21.799
What's Torchwood?
Dunno. special ops.

92
00:08:21.799 --> 00:08:23.439
Yeah. but what does that mean?

93
00:08:23.439 --> 00:08:29.280
Bet you ten quid they're DNA
specialists. it's all DNA these
days. like that CSI bollocks.

94
00:08:29.280 --> 00:08:31.239
CSI Cardiff. I'd like to see that.

95
00:08:31.239 --> 00:08:34.159
They'd be measuring
the velocity of a kebab.

96
00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:40.519
Thank you(!) Break it up!

97
00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:43.399
DOOR SLAMS

98
00:09:44.999 --> 00:09:49.920
Excuse me. It's all sealed off
up there. Who did that?

99
00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:53.839
Thought it was you lot.
But what's it for. what's happened?

100
00:09:53.839 --> 00:09:57.640
9am. it was all sealed off.
they never said.
Chemicals or something.

101
00:10:08.599 --> 00:10:10.119
Hello?

102
00:10:17.719 --> 00:10:20.080
Sorry. I'm just looking for someone.

103
00:10:32.399 --> 00:10:35.320
Right. yeah. Clever.

104
00:10:38.560 --> 00:10:41.599
Anyway. I don't know if you
saw a man come through here -

105
00:10:41.599 --> 00:10:46.880
a tall man. in one of those
big sort of military coats.

106
00:10:54.160 --> 00:10:58.880
OK. If you could answer?
This is official business.

107
00:11:01.720 --> 00:11:03.360
You all right?

108
00:11:07.119 --> 00:11:12.480
That's good.
That's a good mask sort of thing.

109
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:17.280
Look. I'm sorry if I'm
interrupting something. but...

110
00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:19.840
I think we can stop this now. OK?

111
00:11:19.840 --> 00:11:24.999
It's all very well playing silly
buggers. but I'm busy. all right?

112
00:11:26.600 --> 00:11:29.719
Now. I'm looking for a man
in a big grey coat.

113
00:11:32.079 --> 00:11:35.279
I said we can stop being silly.

114
00:11:35.279 --> 00:11:41.880
Ah. there you are. I did ask
when I saw Dr Mahib cos I
thought it was him who said about

115
00:11:41.880 --> 00:11:45.919
the police. but he said no. then I
said about the chemicals but he said
don't be stupid. what chemicals?

116
00:11:45.919 --> 00:11:50.200
So I don't know. could be anything.
who've you got with you there then?
So much for sealing it off.

117
00:11:50.200 --> 00:11:53.119
Ooh. there's a face!

118
00:11:53.119 --> 00:11:58.680
Nice one. Hey. I tell you mate.
you should try plastic surgery.
Not on the NHS mind!

119
00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:01.800
You all right? Yeah.

120
00:12:01.800 --> 00:12:05.199
Bloody hell. that is brilliant.

121
00:12:05.199 --> 00:12:08.440
That's like. em. Hellraiser.

122
00:12:08.440 --> 00:12:13.080
That's first class. that is. Look at
that. it's just like real teeth.

123
00:12:17.479 --> 00:12:20.519
Go! Go! Go!

124
00:12:47.720 --> 00:12:49.759
CAR ENGINE REVS

125
00:13:12.640 --> 00:13:19.560
Registration - Charlie Foxtrot
Zero Six Foxtrot Delta Uniform.

126
00:13:19.560 --> 00:13:24.360
Charlie Foxtrot Zero Six
Foxtrot Delta Uniform. Hold on.
I think Yvonne wants a word.

127
00:13:24.360 --> 00:13:26.440
No sign of a Captain Jack Harkness.

128
00:13:26.440 --> 00:13:28.520
Did you search outside Cardiff?

129
00:13:28.520 --> 00:13:32.080
No. that never occurred to me(!)
Of course I did. I went nationwide.

130
00:13:32.080 --> 00:13:37.279
There's about 15 Jacks and Johns
with that surname. none of them's
a captain. He could've made it up.

131
00:13:37.279 --> 00:13:40.239
The only Captain Jack Harkness
on record was American.

132
00:13:40.239 --> 00:13:45.079
That's it. he's American!
Which you forgot to tell me.
So who is he?

133
00:13:45.079 --> 00:13:48.000
American volunteer. Royal Air Force.
133 Squadron. Except he disappeared.

134
00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:51.240
Vanished off the records.
Presumed dead. When was that?

135
00:13:51.240 --> 00:13:53.280
1941. At the height of the Blitz.

136
00:13:53.280 --> 00:13:58.599
On the morning of January 21 1941.
Captain Jack Harkness
failed to report for duty.

137
00:13:58.599 --> 00:14:00.840
never seen again. till now.

138
00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:04.120
What's going on. Gwen.
you seeing ghosts?

139
00:14:19.919 --> 00:14:22.480
You lot! Oi!

140
00:14:22.480 --> 00:14:24.239
Torchwood!

141
00:14:24.239 --> 00:14:29.400
You can't leave that there.
Police. I can see that. love. and
you're still not leaving it there.

142
00:14:31.920 --> 00:14:34.279
I'm talking to you. Excuse me!

143
00:14:34.279 --> 00:14:35.880
Move your bloody car...

144
00:14:46.119 --> 00:14:49.080
Did you get anything
on that registration?

145
00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:51.319
No such number.

146
00:14:51.319 --> 00:14:53.119
What does that mean?

147
00:14:53.119 --> 00:14:58.240
Doesn't exist. Double checked
with Swansea. triple-checked.
there's nothing. no such vehicle.

148
00:14:58.240 --> 00:15:01.360
But Temple's been asking about
you. Gwen. Are you in trouble?

149
00:15:04.600 --> 00:15:06.240
I have walked.

150
00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:08.520
I have bloody walked.

151
00:15:10.480 --> 00:15:13.399
They were here.
and then they were gone.

152
00:15:13.399 --> 00:15:16.600
And look. there's nowhere to hide.
They just disappeared.

153
00:15:16.600 --> 00:15:19.360
Temple's not just livid.
he's doing his nut.

154
00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:28.079
There was a man. I'm telling you.
there was this porter.
he was in a porter's uniform.

155
00:15:28.079 --> 00:15:31.080
and he was killed.
or at least he was injured.

156
00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:37.039
he must've been injured. right
in front of me. this man in a
mask. sort of lashed out. and...

157
00:15:37.039 --> 00:15:41.839
And I've told you. all
hospital staff. present and correct.

158
00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:48.960
I saw it. That's it? Gwen.
sweetheart. think about it.
what sort of story is that?

159
00:15:50.040 --> 00:15:53.119
You're not well. Come with me.
I'll take you home.

160
00:15:54.880 --> 00:15:57.600
They were here. Come on.

161
00:16:12.600 --> 00:16:16.200
Look at me! Hot pot!

162
00:16:16.200 --> 00:16:19.279
Or. as the French call it. ho po.

163
00:16:19.279 --> 00:16:23.200
Oh. I should've phoned.
I've got to work.

164
00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:25.199
You should be off sick.

165
00:16:25.199 --> 00:16:28.279
I know. but they were short
and there's a match on tonight.

166
00:16:28.279 --> 00:16:31.439
so I said I'd take another shift.
I'm sorry.

167
00:16:31.439 --> 00:16:33.919
Forgive me.

168
00:16:33.919 --> 00:16:38.200
Go on. forgive me. Say you
forgive me. you do. don't you?

169
00:16:40.480 --> 00:16:42.840
OK I got to go.

170
00:17:28.440 --> 00:17:31.000
Excuse me. Gwen Cooper. CID.

171
00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:36.000
I'm making some enquiries round the
Bay. I need to check some people
out on your list. if that's OK.

172
00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:39.480
I don't suppose you deliver
to a Captain Jack Harkness?

173
00:17:39.480 --> 00:17:42.199
I dunno.
Well. could you have a look?

174
00:17:43.719 --> 00:17:45.600
Nope.

175
00:17:45.600 --> 00:17:47.920
He's not a regular anyway.

176
00:17:47.920 --> 00:17:50.200
J Harkness? Or just Harkness?

177
00:17:56.640 --> 00:17:57.679
No.

178
00:17:57.679 --> 00:18:00.800
OK. Never mind. Thanks anyway.

179
00:18:02.599 --> 00:18:08.200
I don't suppose you've got a
Torchwood? Oh. aye. we do them all
the time. They're good customers.

180
00:18:38.959 --> 00:18:46.639
Oh. hiya. Sorry I'm late.
Someone ordered pizza. Who's it for?
I think it's a...Mr Harkness.

181
00:18:57.760 --> 00:18:59.440
Don't keep them waiting.

182
00:21:05.000 --> 00:21:06.760
SHE LAUGHS

183
00:21:06.760 --> 00:21:08.640
I can't do this. I'm sorry.

184
00:21:08.640 --> 00:21:10.400
I'm rubbish. I give up!

185
00:21:10.400 --> 00:21:14.520
He set me off. Well. that lasted
nought point two seconds.

186
00:21:14.520 --> 00:21:17.280
She's actually carrying pizza!

187
00:21:17.280 --> 00:21:22.240
Come on! She was gonna say.
"Here's your pizza." and I was going
to say. "How much?" and she says.

188
00:21:22.240 --> 00:21:24.439
"Oh. whatever. twenty quid."

189
00:21:24.439 --> 00:21:28.640
and I say. "Oh. I don't have any
money." I was working on a punchline.

190
00:21:28.640 --> 00:21:31.520
I'd have got there.
But it would've been good!

191
00:21:31.520 --> 00:21:34.840
There's your pizza. I'd better go.
We've gone past that stage.

192
00:21:34.840 --> 00:21:39.399
You must've been freezing out there.
How long were you walking around?
Three hours? You could see me?

193
00:21:39.399 --> 00:21:44.040
And before we go any further.
who the hell orders pizza
under the name of Torchwood?

194
00:21:44.040 --> 00:21:47.919
Me. I'm sorry. I'm a twat.

195
00:21:47.919 --> 00:21:53.999
That man. at the hospital.
that porter. what happened to him?

196
00:21:53.999 --> 00:21:59.680
That was real. wasn't it?
He was attacked. He's dead.
But there's no-one gone missing.

197
00:21:59.680 --> 00:22:05.160
We took the body. changed the work
rota. planted a false witness
who saw him leaving the hospital.

198
00:22:05.160 --> 00:22:07.759
giving him an alibi
for the next 48 hours.

199
00:22:07.759 --> 00:22:12.319
so when his body's pulled out of the
docks next Tuesday night. he's only
been missing for three days.

200
00:22:12.319 --> 00:22:15.799
He was murdered? Yes. And you
covered it up? That's my job.

201
00:22:18.560 --> 00:22:23.560
And that other man. John Tucker?
Last night in the alleyway.
I saw you. And what did you see?

202
00:22:23.560 --> 00:22:26.320
You revived him. No.

203
00:22:26.320 --> 00:22:29.239
What did you see?
You resuscitated him.

204
00:22:29.239 --> 00:22:32.959
No. what did you see?

205
00:22:32.959 --> 00:22:36.280
You brought him back to life. Yeah.

206
00:22:37.999 --> 00:22:39.760
Who are you?

207
00:22:39.760 --> 00:22:44.480
Torchwood. What's Torchwood?
This is Torchwood.

208
00:22:44.480 --> 00:22:47.400
All around you.

209
00:22:47.400 --> 00:22:52.320
And what happens to me? I'm police.
Constable Gwen Cooper.

210
00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:54.759
You can't do anything.

211
00:22:55.560 --> 00:22:58.920
Right then. PC Cooper...

212
00:23:00.840 --> 00:23:03.200
..d'you want to come see?

213
00:23:03.200 --> 00:23:05.880
See what? You saw the murder.

214
00:23:07.320 --> 00:23:09.480
Come and see the murderer.

215
00:23:14.080 --> 00:23:16.359
Go with him.

216
00:23:19.480 --> 00:23:24.840
What is Torchwood? Who are you?
What is this place?
SCREECHING

217
00:23:24.840 --> 00:23:27.280
What was that? Pterodactyl.

218
00:23:27.280 --> 00:23:30.279
Are you coming?

219
00:23:49.640 --> 00:23:54.799
It's all right -
it's safe. it's sedated.

220
00:23:58.159 --> 00:24:00.520
It's called a Weevil.

221
00:24:00.520 --> 00:24:02.719
Or at least. we call them Weevils.

222
00:24:02.719 --> 00:24:06.600
We don't know their real name.
cos they're not too
good at communicating.

223
00:24:06.600 --> 00:24:12.360
But we've got a couple
of hundred of them in the city living
in the sewers. feeding off the...

224
00:24:12.360 --> 00:24:14.719
Well. it's the sewers.

225
00:24:14.719 --> 00:24:16.520
you can guess.

226
00:24:16.520 --> 00:24:22.039
But every once in a while.
one of them goes rogue.
comes to the surface. attacks.

227
00:24:22.039 --> 00:24:26.680
Actually. it's been happening more
and more and we have no idea why.

228
00:24:26.680 --> 00:24:29.039
But it's alien.

229
00:24:29.039 --> 00:24:32.079
Look into its eyes.

230
00:24:43.039 --> 00:24:45.039
There you go.

231
00:24:48.559 --> 00:24:50.120
Take your time.

232
00:24:54.959 --> 00:24:57.159
It was born on a different world

233
00:24:57.159 --> 00:24:59.040
and it's real.

234
00:25:06.080 --> 00:25:08.959
Owen Harper. Gwen Cooper.
"Doctor" Owen Harper. thank you.

235
00:25:08.959 --> 00:25:12.919
Toshiko Sato. Suzie Costello.
she's second-in-command.

236
00:25:12.919 --> 00:25:20.640
And this is Ianto Jones.
Ianto cleans up after us and gets us
everywhere on time. I try my best.

237
00:25:20.640 --> 00:25:24.120
And he looks good in a suit.
Careful. that's harassment. sir.

238
00:25:24.120 --> 00:25:26.359
Why are you telling me their names?

239
00:25:26.359 --> 00:25:31.360
I'm not supposed to know. am I?
This is classified. isn't it?
Way beyond classified.

240
00:25:31.360 --> 00:25:34.840
Then you shouldn't be telling me.
What are you gonna do to me?

241
00:25:34.840 --> 00:25:40.239
What d'you imagine? Well. I've
seen too much. Your names and
everything. and the Weevil. and...

242
00:25:40.239 --> 00:25:43.480
You can dump a man in the water
and lie about his death.

243
00:25:43.480 --> 00:25:49.640
OK! Tosh. finish that calibration
tomorrow morning. Owen. first thing.
get a hold of Chandler and Bell.

244
00:25:49.640 --> 00:25:54.879
cos I think they're lying.
Ianto. if he needs back-up. then
you'd better be on stand-by. Suzie.

245
00:25:54.879 --> 00:26:00.439
I know it's a pain in the ass.
but I need the costing on the glove
research. and you're coming with me.

246
00:26:02.839 --> 00:26:06.120
I'm getting tired of following you.

247
00:26:06.120 --> 00:26:09.920
No you're not. and you never will.

248
00:26:11.440 --> 00:26:14.759
Stand on here. C'mon. next to me.

249
00:26:14.759 --> 00:26:16.040
Good night!

250
00:26:17.199 --> 00:26:20.640
Now. you came in
through the front door.

251
00:26:20.640 --> 00:26:23.520
Let's take the scenic route.

252
00:26:59.680 --> 00:27:03.720
But they can see the lift.

253
00:27:03.720 --> 00:27:07.400
Why aren't they...?

254
00:27:07.400 --> 00:27:10.799
We're right out in the open.
They can see everything!

255
00:27:10.799 --> 00:27:15.879
Do they look like they can see us?
No. but... Look at us! We couldn't
be any more public! Hello!

256
00:27:15.879 --> 00:27:19.000
Hey. you there. hello!

257
00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:24.239
It's called a perception filter.
He can sort of see us.
but we don't quite register.

258
00:27:24.239 --> 00:27:27.000
Just like something
in the corner of your eye.

259
00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:34.039
It only works on this exact spot.
Step off... Hi! Nice night!

260
00:27:34.039 --> 00:27:36.120
And lo. we are perceived.

261
00:27:37.679 --> 00:27:42.040
How does it work? No idea. We know
how to use it. not how it happens.

262
00:27:42.040 --> 00:27:46.200
But if I were to guess. I'd say
that there was once a dimensionally
transcendental chameleon-circuit

263
00:27:46.200 --> 00:27:52.639
placed right on this spot which
welded its perception properties
to a spatio-temporal rift.

264
00:27:52.639 --> 00:27:54.840
But that sounds kind of ridiculous.

265
00:27:54.840 --> 00:28:00.519
"Invisible lift" has got more of
a ring to it. But if no-one can see
it when the lift's coming up.

266
00:28:00.519 --> 00:28:03.799
there's a bloody big hole in
the floor. don't people fall in?

267
00:28:03.799 --> 00:28:06.040
That is so Welsh. What is?

268
00:28:06.040 --> 00:28:09.439
I show you something fantastic -
you find fault.

269
00:28:31.480 --> 00:28:35.399
I just don't understand...
I tell you what I don't understand.

270
00:28:35.399 --> 00:28:39.960
You're gonna rattle on with that.
"How can this be true?"
What's it gonna take for you people?

271
00:28:39.960 --> 00:28:45.039
If you want evidence of aliens. how
about that great spaceship hovering
over London on Christmas Day?

272
00:28:45.039 --> 00:28:47.959
What about the battle of Canary
Wharf? A Cyberman in every home!

273
00:28:47.959 --> 00:28:53.119
My boyfriend says it's like a sort
of terrorism. Like they put drugs
in the water supplies -

274
00:28:53.119 --> 00:28:57.440
psychotropic drugs. causing
mass hallucinations and stuff.

275
00:28:57.440 --> 00:29:00.960
Yeah. well your boyfriend's stupid.
Oh. you've met him?

276
00:29:07.080 --> 00:29:10.639
So...you catch aliens?

277
00:29:10.639 --> 00:29:12.799
Yup. You catch aliens for a living?

278
00:29:12.799 --> 00:29:16.240
Yes. we do. You're an alien-catcher?
Yes. I am. Caught any good aliens?

279
00:29:16.240 --> 00:29:18.799
Tons of 'em! That's hell of a job.
Sure is.

280
00:29:22.560 --> 00:29:24.360
This is so weird.

281
00:29:26.400 --> 00:29:32.119
And who are you. then?
Captain Jack Harkness.

282
00:29:32.119 --> 00:29:37.039
I did some research
and there's only one Captain
Jack Harkness on record.

283
00:29:37.039 --> 00:29:44.199
And he disappeared in 1941. Well...
that couldn't be me...could it?

284
00:29:47.559 --> 00:29:50.359
We don't just catch aliens.

285
00:29:50.359 --> 00:29:52.680
We scavenge the stuff
they leave behind.

286
00:29:52.680 --> 00:29:56.160
Find ways of using it.
Arming the human race for the future.

287
00:29:56.160 --> 00:30:01.320
The twenty-first century is when it
all changes. and you've got to be
ready. But who's in charge of you?

288
00:30:01.320 --> 00:30:05.760
We're separate from the government.
Outside the police.
Beyond the United Nations.

289
00:30:05.760 --> 00:30:12.160
Cos if one power got hold of this
stuff. they could use it for
their own purposes. But so could you.

290
00:30:12.160 --> 00:30:17.359
All alien technology stays
on the base. No-one's allowed
to take anything outside.

291
00:30:53.119 --> 00:30:56.959
So go on. then. How the hell
did you end up in Cardiff?

292
00:30:56.959 --> 00:31:02.839
This is Torchwood Three.
Torchwood One was London.
destroyed in the battle.

293
00:31:02.839 --> 00:31:07.919
Torchwood Two is an office
in Glasgow. very strange man.

294
00:31:07.919 --> 00:31:12.680
Torchwood three. Cardiff.
Torchwood Four's kinda gone missing.
but we'll find it one day.

295
00:31:12.680 --> 00:31:14.639
So you just fancied Cardiff?

296
00:31:14.639 --> 00:31:18.639
There's a rift in space and time
running right through the city.

297
00:31:18.639 --> 00:31:22.999
The Weevils didn't come in a
spaceship. They just slip through.

298
00:31:22.999 --> 00:31:25.240
All sorts of things
get washed up here.

299
00:31:25.240 --> 00:31:31.560
Creatures. timeshifts.
space junk. debris. flotsam and
jetsam. Sounds like Cardiff. yeah.

300
00:31:31.560 --> 00:31:34.200
Hey. don't knock it. I'm a citizen.

301
00:31:34.200 --> 00:31:36.360
But where are you from?

302
00:31:36.360 --> 00:31:39.840
All sorts of places.

303
00:31:39.840 --> 00:31:42.120
Thing is. we could liaise on this...

304
00:31:42.120 --> 00:31:47.160
the serial killer. I could be like
your liaison with the police.

305
00:31:47.160 --> 00:31:49.679
Right. I can see the mistake.

306
00:31:49.679 --> 00:31:53.719
You think because we showed up
we're out to catch the killer.

307
00:31:53.719 --> 00:31:58.519
Sorry. Nothing to do with us.
Then what were you doing there?
Testing the glove.

308
00:31:59.520 --> 00:32:03.399
We need murder victims.
simple as that. The glove
only works on the recently deceased.

309
00:32:03.399 --> 00:32:06.759
and the more violent the trauma.
the stronger the resurrection.
All we need is fresh meat.

310
00:32:06.759 --> 00:32:11.720
No. you were asking that man.
John Tucker. I saw you. you were
asking him about his killer.

311
00:32:11.720 --> 00:32:16.000
He'd just been murdered.
what else are you gonna ask? You
could get an ID. You could help.

312
00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:20.960
We're busy. And your work is more
important? Now you've got it.

313
00:32:20.960 --> 00:32:26.120
Well. that's tough shit. Cos if
you let me go. then I have a duty.
cos that glove could help us.

314
00:32:27.840 --> 00:32:31.039
If you remember. What d'you mean?

315
00:32:31.039 --> 00:32:33.240
How's your drink?

316
00:32:37.640 --> 00:32:42.840
Have you poisoned me? Don't be so
dramatic. It's an amnesia pill.

317
00:32:42.840 --> 00:32:45.839
My own recipe. with a touch
of denial and a dash of retcon.

318
00:32:45.839 --> 00:32:49.199
Wake up tomorrow morning. you'll have
forgotten everything about Torchwood.

319
00:32:49.199 --> 00:32:51.240
Worse still.
you'll have forgotten me...

320
00:32:53.920 --> 00:32:55.719
..which is kind of tragic.

321
00:33:02.080 --> 00:33:04.719
Don't think you can fight it
by staying awake.

322
00:33:04.719 --> 00:33:06.840
I mixed in a little
bit of sedative too.

323
00:33:06.840 --> 00:33:11.439
Then I'll tell someone! D'you really
want us to come and find them too?

324
00:33:11.439 --> 00:33:14.400
You bastard. Language!

325
00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:16.800
Nice knowing you. Gwen Cooper.

326
00:34:12.799 --> 00:34:14.839
Hello. All right?

327
00:34:14.839 --> 00:34:20.959
You having a good time? I was.
Can I buy you a drink?

328
00:34:20.959 --> 00:34:23.759
No. thanks. I'm fine.

329
00:34:25.879 --> 00:34:27.480
Am I wasting my time?

330
00:34:27.480 --> 00:34:30.520
I dunno. are you?

331
00:34:33.120 --> 00:34:38.479
I've got to be up early and I've got
hell of a day tomorrow and I can't
be bothered with all the chat.

332
00:34:44.880 --> 00:34:48.559
So...do you want a drink or what?

333
00:34:57.799 --> 00:35:03.520
Bloody hell fire. You're coming
home with me. you are. Right now!

334
00:36:13.479 --> 00:36:18.880
Oi. you bastard. come here!
Linda. what the fuck
do you think you are doing?!

335
00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:21.679
I'm taking him home
and I'm having him. now piss off!

336
00:36:21.679 --> 00:36:26.200
What the fuck d'you think you're
doing with my girlfriend? Hey. she
was on her own. She never said.

337
00:36:26.200 --> 00:36:29.880
You fucking tosser.
Colin. button it. he's mine.

338
00:36:29.880 --> 00:36:35.479
Do you want to have a go? You want
to have a go? Come on then mate!
Well. if it makes it easier...

339
00:36:41.799 --> 00:36:44.520
I am so having you.

340
00:36:44.520 --> 00:36:47.040
I'm having him first! Taxi!

341
00:38:24.199 --> 00:38:28.960
Did you get pissed? No.

342
00:38:28.960 --> 00:38:32.079
What time is it?

343
00:38:32.079 --> 00:38:33.720
Seven thirty.

344
00:38:33.720 --> 00:38:38.280
You said you were working
last night. I was.

345
00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:40.759
Then how come
you fell asleep in here?

346
00:38:40.759 --> 00:38:44.800
I haven't. I was...typing.

347
00:38:44.800 --> 00:38:47.119
That is work.

348
00:38:47.119 --> 00:38:49.800
I'm not having a go. I'm just saying.

349
00:38:49.800 --> 00:38:53.719
Not exactly clever going out on the
lash when you've just had
a bang on the head.

350
00:38:53.719 --> 00:38:58.119
I hope you didn't drive in that
state. Who were you with? Diane?

351
00:38:58.119 --> 00:39:00.680
Must've been. Yeah.

352
00:39:05.679 --> 00:39:08.679
Have any luck? With what?

353
00:39:08.679 --> 00:39:10.879
Captain Jack Harkness.

354
00:39:10.879 --> 00:39:17.679
How d'you mean? Who's he?
Oh. well don't worry about me.
just go ahead. wasting my time.

355
00:39:29.519 --> 00:39:33.040
Aye. aye. Come to see
where the real work's done?

356
00:39:33.040 --> 00:39:38.080
Yes. sir. that's right. sir.
How's it going? Sod all.

357
00:39:42.319 --> 00:39:48.840
Is that the murder weapon?
Clever. mind.
they worked it all out on a computer.

358
00:39:48.840 --> 00:39:54.400
Took measurements from the stab
wounds. calculated the shape
of the blade and stuff.

359
00:39:54.400 --> 00:39:57.600
even those prongs -
I don't know how they do it.

360
00:39:57.600 --> 00:40:00.359
Nasty-looking beast. though.

361
00:40:00.359 --> 00:40:06.240
D'you recognise it? No.
We're trying to trace it.
Can't be that many of 'em.

362
00:40:06.240 --> 00:40:11.640
Sort of ornamental.
We're checking the CDE logs with
customs in case it's been imported.

363
00:40:11.640 --> 00:40:13.800
Find the knife.
we might find the killer.

364
00:40:13.800 --> 00:40:19.400
Anyway. if it rings any bells.
give's a shout. Yeah. Thanks.

365
00:40:33.600 --> 00:40:36.039
..I said to Geoff.
it's not demotion being put in goal.

366
00:40:36.039 --> 00:40:39.000
it's vital.
but was he having any of it?

367
00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:42.679
He's off and moaning. says. who
books the ground. who pays the subs?

368
00:40:42.679 --> 00:40:46.039
And all the time.
he's wheezing away.

369
00:40:46.039 --> 00:40:48.319
and I'm like. Geoff.
you're proving my point mate...

370
00:40:48.319 --> 00:40:55.919
"You never come down. you're in
charge of transport." I said. "Mam.
I can't go hopping on a truck!"

371
00:40:55.919 --> 00:41:01.399
All that Christmas stuff.
all over again. I was like.
for God's sake. leave it...

372
00:43:19.880 --> 00:43:23.200
Hello again. You were right.

373
00:43:23.200 --> 00:43:28.879
You told Jack we should
liaise with the police.
I was the only one who bothered.

374
00:43:28.879 --> 00:43:32.359
So I was the only one
who saw the report.

375
00:43:34.760 --> 00:43:39.360
They got a good likeness.
I'm arresting you for...

376
00:43:39.360 --> 00:43:45.359
How do I know you? I thought you saw
it. And that can trip the amnesia.
one image. if you're clever.

377
00:43:45.359 --> 00:43:48.000
He said you were good.

378
00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:52.520
Anyway. It's not much good
now. I can't really...

379
00:43:52.520 --> 00:43:57.639
But you're gonna put up a fight.
So I've got...

380
00:43:57.639 --> 00:43:59.839
Um. Hold on. Sorry.

381
00:44:04.320 --> 00:44:06.159
There. That's better.

382
00:44:06.159 --> 00:44:09.800
Put it down. You had to come back.
Put down the gun.

383
00:44:09.800 --> 00:44:15.199
You're the only one
who can make the link.
Well. the only one in public.

384
00:44:15.199 --> 00:44:20.320
Torchwood's gonna find out
by morning. but I'll be gone.

385
00:44:20.320 --> 00:44:23.440
I don't know where. Far away.

386
00:44:23.440 --> 00:44:25.800
What am I gonna do?

387
00:44:27.319 --> 00:44:30.040
I loved this job. I really loved it.

388
00:44:30.040 --> 00:44:34.039
And now I've got to run.

389
00:44:34.039 --> 00:44:36.999
Oh. Christ.

390
00:44:36.999 --> 00:44:43.119
How can you do any other job
after this one? Please. Put down
the gun. Cos it gets inside you.

391
00:44:43.119 --> 00:44:46.920
You do this job for long
enough. and you end up thinking.

392
00:44:46.920 --> 00:44:51.640
"How come we get all
the Weevils and bollocks and shit?"

393
00:44:51.640 --> 00:44:54.600
Is that what alien life is? Filth?

394
00:44:54.600 --> 00:44:59.439
But maybe there's better stuff
out there. brilliant stuff.

395
00:44:59.439 --> 00:45:01.560
beautiful stuff. Just...

396
00:45:01.560 --> 00:45:04.559
they don't come here.

397
00:45:06.520 --> 00:45:09.919
This planet's so dirty.
that's all we get - the shit.

398
00:45:09.919 --> 00:45:15.360
I don't know what you're talking
about. I wish I could forget.

399
00:45:15.360 --> 00:45:20.199
Why did you kill those people?
For the glove. Stay where you are.

400
00:45:20.199 --> 00:45:23.359
I needed the bodies.
That's how it works. Violent death.

401
00:45:23.359 --> 00:45:28.359
And it was so easy. To bring them
back. I'd position myself behind the
head. so they'd never see me twice.

402
00:45:28.359 --> 00:45:31.800
You killed three people.
It was the only way.

403
00:45:31.800 --> 00:45:36.559
The more I use the glove.
the more I control it. I don't
understand. what glove?

404
00:45:36.559 --> 00:45:39.960
If I can get enough practice.
then think what that glove could do.

405
00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:44.479
If I could get it work all the time.
on anything. beyond the two minutes.
if it could work permanently.

406
00:45:44.479 --> 00:45:46.159
it could resurrect.

407
00:45:46.159 --> 00:45:50.080
Resurrection on demand for
the whole world. isn't that good?

408
00:45:50.080 --> 00:45:55.359
Isn't it though? Well. that's what
I've been working for.
all day and all night.

409
00:45:55.359 --> 00:45:59.200
The rest of them
go swanning about. but I'm working.

410
00:45:59.200 --> 00:46:03.879
You've got to get inside this stuff.
Surrender yourself to it.

411
00:46:03.879 --> 00:46:09.280
I did. with the knife. and the
glove. and that's why the perception
filter isn't gonna work on me.

412
00:46:12.719 --> 00:46:15.480
Where did he come from?

413
00:46:16.800 --> 00:46:19.639
What have you done?

414
00:46:20.719 --> 00:46:23.559
Please don't. I can't let you go.

415
00:46:23.559 --> 00:46:26.280
Please. I've got to.

416
00:46:26.280 --> 00:46:27.720
I'm sorry.

417
00:46:27.720 --> 00:46:30.360
Don't. don't. don't.

418
00:46:30.360 --> 00:46:32.479
I've got to. I've got to.
I've got to.

419
00:46:37.359 --> 00:46:39.319
Put down the gun.

420
00:46:46.360 --> 00:46:50.040
Susie. it's over. Now. come with me.

421
00:47:07.560 --> 00:47:11.440
I remember. I remember.

422
00:47:15.360 --> 00:47:17.640
I remember.

423
00:48:14.680 --> 00:48:20.200
Owen and Toshiko. you didn't tell
them that you were shot in the head
and survived.

424
00:48:20.200 --> 00:48:24.079
You didn't tell them either.
Followed my lead.

425
00:48:24.999 --> 00:48:29.480
Keep doing that. and you
might just get through this.

426
00:48:29.480 --> 00:48:32.119
But she killed you.

427
00:48:34.599 --> 00:48:37.080
I can't die.

428
00:48:37.080 --> 00:48:39.679
OK. But I can't.

429
00:48:41.560 --> 00:48:46.039
Something happened to me a while
back. Long story. And far away.

430
00:48:47.599 --> 00:48:49.160
But I was killed.

431
00:48:49.160 --> 00:48:53.080
and then I was brought back
to life. and ever since then...

432
00:48:53.080 --> 00:48:55.800
I can't die.

433
00:48:55.800 --> 00:48:58.760
But how? I don't know.

434
00:48:58.760 --> 00:49:04.559
One day. I'll find a doctor.
the right sort of doctor and maybe he
can explain it. But until then...

435
00:49:04.559 --> 00:49:06.159
Nothing kills you?

436
00:49:06.159 --> 00:49:09.480
Kind of freaks people out. so...

437
00:49:09.480 --> 00:49:12.559
Best if you don't say anything.

438
00:49:12.559 --> 00:49:14.120
It doesn't matter anyway.

439
00:49:14.120 --> 00:49:17.480
You'll only wipe my memory again.
Why would I do that?

440
00:49:19.119 --> 00:49:21.880
Torchwood's got a vacancy.

441
00:49:21.880 --> 00:49:24.799
Job going spare. Do you want it?

442
00:49:24.799 --> 00:49:27.960
But what d'you need me for?

443
00:49:27.960 --> 00:49:30.880
Cos maybe you were right.

444
00:49:30.880 --> 00:49:33.240
We could do more to help.

445
